  "Title": "Allow Scribe in Sharepoint allow list for embedding Scribes in iFrames.",
  "Description": "<p>Hello Systems!&nbsp; Our final Scribe POC sync meeting is dependent on Scribe being enabled for Sharepoint.&nbsp; This is a key feature for us, as embedding scribes in a sharepoint page gives us a rudimentary security boundary, and obscures URL's.&nbsp; This is our preferred way of publishing scribes.&nbsp; I've included some CoPilot instructions below.&nbsp; Thank you!!!<br><br>Allowing iFrame Embeds from ScribeHow in SharePoint Online</p><p>Overview</p><p>To enable SharePoint Online to embed content from <strong>scribehow.com</strong>, you must add the domain to the <strong>HTML Field Security</strong> allowΓÇælist at the <strong>site collection level</strong>. This requires SharePoint admin permissions.</p><p>Steps to Allow ScribeHow iFrames:</p><p>1. Open the Root Site of Your SharePoint Collection</p><p>Navigate to:<br><code>https://.sharepoint.com/</code></p><p>2. Access Site Settings</p><ul>\t<li>Select <strong>Settings (gear icon)</strong> ΓåÆ <strong>Site settings</strong></li>\t<li>If not visible: choose <strong>Site information</strong> ΓåÆ <strong>View all site settings</strong></li></ul><p>3. Open HTML Field Security</p><p>Under <strong>Site Collection Administration</strong>, select:<br><strong>HTML Field Security</strong></p><p>4. Adjust iFrame Permissions</p><p>Choose the option:<br><strong>Allow contributors to insert iframes from the following list of domains</strong></p><p>5. Add ScribeHow Domains</p><p>Add the following entries:</p><ul>\t<li><code>https://scribehow.com</code></li>\t<li><code>https://www.scribehow.com</code></li></ul><p>6. Save Your Changes</p><p>Once saved, SharePoint will allow embedding ScribeHow content using the <strong>Embed</strong> web part.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Notes</p><ul>\t<li>These settings apply <strong>per site collection</strong>. Repeat for any additional sites.</li>\t<li>Microsoft Lists inherits the same HTML Field Security rules.</li>\t<li>TenantΓÇælevel restrictions may override site settings.</li></ul>",
